@jnicklas We could (without any change to the public API behavior) unify the spec to say: `html` (and synonymously `body` and `source`) return the state of the DOM. And in case of RackTest, we do the next most sensible thing and return the original source.

The current differentiation (original source vs. DOM) doesn't really make much sense IMO, since not one driver actually has different behavior for those methods.

Thoughts?

